Now, if either the NID or memcg changes, we batch process any folios that have been put on the list. Important to note: we add the folio to `migrate_list`, and then `folio_put(folio)`.

Wait a minute... we're dropping the `folio_try_get()` reference *after* we've possibly isolated the folio. This implies we are only holding a reference via isolation. But `migrate_misplaced_folios_batch` expects the folio to have an elevated reference from isolation. We're dropping the only reference we had, so the only reference left will be the one `folio_isolate_lru()` set when isolating.

